id: pm-fjxm
title: "GH-509: pm claim --next lacks candidate filters and race-loss walk — thread next filters + advance to next candidate"
description: "GH-509 (filed against npm v2026.7.10, which predates PR#502). The base atomic primitive ALREADY shipped: pm claim --next atomically recommends+claims under one lock (pm-114v, PR#502, 2026-07-10). The issue's remaining delta on main: (1) claim --next accepts NONE of pm next's candidate filters (--type/--tag/--priority/--assignee-filter/--parent/--sprint/--release) so a worker cannot scope to its lane — verified via pm claim --help on main 2026-07-11; (2) on race loss the loser fails (exit 4) instead of transparently advancing to the next ready candidate — issue proposes walk-with-bound via --max-attempts <n> / --if-available semantics (claim --next already has --if-available for the single-item case); (3) canonical single-call worker loop: while item=$(pm claim --next --author $AGENT --type task --json); do ...; done. Spelling decision (next --claim vs extending claim --next) belongs to ADR pm-pbyu grammar rules — prefer extending the existing claim --next verb, do not mint a second spelling. Interacts with pm-eqk0: any candidate-walk must ALSO skip Decision-type items or the walk funnels every lane into an unresolvable ADR."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,cli,concurrency,multi-agent
created_at: "2026-07-11T03:05:51.194Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-11T19:44:11.123Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-11T19:44:10.091Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "pm claim --next accepts the full pm next candidate-filter set (type/tag/priority/assignee-filter/parent/sprint/release) and scopes ranking identically to pm next; on losing the claim race, claim --next advances to the next ready candidate under the same lock semantics, bounded by --max-attempts (default documented); exhausting candidates returns a distinct non-error empty result usable in shell while-loops; contracts/completions/docs/MCP schema updated per new-flag wiring checklist; no second command spelling introduced"
parent: pm-dj98
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: claim --next supports filtered bounded walking and an explicit empty if-available result.
expected_result: "Fleet workers can scope, atomically claim, and stop cleanly when their lane is exhausted."
actual_result: "Filtered claims walk bounded candidates; --if-available returns available:false and item:null on exhaustion."
